WEBVTT

00:07.508 --> 00:10.144
Neal: THERE IS NO SECURITY
ON THIS EARTH, ONLY OPPORTUNITY.

00:10.178 --> 00:11.979
Sara: THAT IS NOT
WHAT I WANT TO HEAR

00:12.012 --> 00:14.215
FROM THE MAN I'M ASKING
TO CONSULT ON MY SECURITY.

00:14.248 --> 00:15.516
WELL,
YOU GOT TO LOVE IRONY.

00:15.549 --> 00:16.550
WHAT'S THE EVENT?

00:16.584 --> 00:18.018
IT'S TOMORROW'S
LAUNCH PARTY

00:18.052 --> 00:19.987
FOR PARFUM BIJOUX'S
NEW FRAGRANCE LINE,

00:20.020 --> 00:22.156
INSPIRED BY THE BLEND WORE
BY MARIE ANTOINETTE.

00:22.190 --> 00:24.058
WHERE ELSE WOULD
THE NEW LINE BE-HEADED?

00:24.092 --> 00:25.326
OH.
YEAH.

00:25.359 --> 00:27.195
WELL, AT LEAST YOU DIDN'T ASK
IF IT SMELLS LIKE CAKE.

00:27.228 --> 00:28.396
EH,
THAT'S TOO OBVIOUS.

00:28.429 --> 00:30.498
THEY'RE DISPLAYING
THE ORIGINAL FORMULA

00:30.531 --> 00:33.567
IN ITS ORIGINAL ATOMIZER ON LOAN
FROM THE MARQUISE DE TOURZEL,

00:33.601 --> 00:35.536
AND FULLY INSURED
BY STERLING BOSCH.

00:35.569 --> 00:38.072
YOU HAVE A DATE
TO THIS LITTLE SOIREE?

00:38.106 --> 00:39.840
WOULD IT MATTER
IF I DID?

00:39.873 --> 00:40.908
NOT AT ALL.

00:40.941 --> 00:42.676
WE AGREED
TO KEEP THIS CASUAL.

00:42.710 --> 00:43.677
YEAH...

00:43.711 --> 00:46.214
WE DID.

00:50.951 --> 00:52.853
[ LAUGHS ]

00:52.886 --> 00:54.188
AMIS-AMANTS.

00:54.222 --> 00:57.891
AMIS-AMANTS --
"FRIENDS WHO HAVE FUN."

00:57.925 --> 00:59.427
[ SIGHS ] THE FRENCH
HAVE A WORD FOR EVERYTHING.

00:59.460 --> 01:00.528
MM-HMM.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.430
I MIGHT
STOP BY AFTERWARDS.

01:02.463 --> 01:04.532
I MIGHT
MAKE YOU A LATE DINNER.

01:04.565 --> 01:05.599
YEAH?
YEAH.

01:05.633 --> 01:07.701
THAT'S HOW
THIS WHOLE THING GOT STARTED.

01:07.735 --> 01:10.604
I WANTED TO THANK YOU FOR
HELPING WITH THE DELANCY CASE.
OH.

01:10.638 --> 01:12.873
SEE, I THOUGHT THE THANK-YOU
WAS WHAT CAME AFTER DINNER.

01:12.906 --> 01:14.908
THEN YOU'LL HAVE TO THANK ME
FOR HELPING WITH THE SECURITY.

01:14.942 --> 01:16.444
MM-HMM.

01:18.412 --> 01:19.613
I BETTER NOT
MESS THIS UP.
DON'T.

01:19.647 --> 01:20.614
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

01:20.648 --> 01:22.049
OKAY,
SHOULD I BE THINKING

01:22.082 --> 01:24.118
FIVE-STAR RESTAURANT
OR CAPE COD CLAMBAKE?

01:24.152 --> 01:26.254
YES.
HONEY, COME ON!
ONE HINT!

01:26.287 --> 01:29.056
HON, THE WHOLE POINT
OF A SURPRISE GETAWAY --

01:29.089 --> 01:31.559
IT'S A SURPRISE, I KNOW,
BUT DO YOU REALLY WANT TO BE

01:31.592 --> 01:33.894
LUGGING AROUND
MY ENTIRE WARDROBE FOR TWO DAYS?

01:33.927 --> 01:35.129
WELL,
LUCKILY FOR YOU,

01:35.163 --> 01:37.064
I HAVE THE UPPER-BODY STRENGTH
OF A NORSE GOD.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.065
[ LAUGHS ]

01:38.098 --> 01:39.233
OH,
AND YOU DON'T MIND

01:39.267 --> 01:40.768
IF WE GO BY
THE PARFUM BIJOUX EVENT, RIGHT?

01:40.801 --> 01:41.969
JUST FOR
TWO MINUTES.

01:42.002 --> 01:43.904
TWO MINUTES? NO.
TWO HOURS? YES.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.240
OH, HONEY,
IT'S REALLY IMPORTANT TO SARA.

01:46.274 --> 01:47.808
YES,
AND SHE'S A BIG GIRL,

01:47.841 --> 01:50.444
AND IT'S NOT NEARLY
AS IMPORTANT AS YOU AND I

01:50.478 --> 01:51.945
FINALLY GETTING SOME TIME AWAY
WITH NO DISTRACTIONS.

01:51.979 --> 01:53.281
I KNOW. YOU'RE RIGHT.

01:53.314 --> 01:55.416
WE PROMISED EACH OTHER
NO WORK TALK.

01:55.449 --> 01:56.450
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

01:56.484 --> 01:58.252
WHO'S THAT?
OH, THAT'S JONES.

01:58.286 --> 02:00.454
HE'S HERE TO...
NOT TALK
ABOUT WORK?

02:00.488 --> 02:02.122
I'LL MAKE IT QUICK.
MM-HMM.

02:04.992 --> 02:06.994
AND DON'T BOTHER
LOOKING IN MY BAG.

02:07.027 --> 02:09.129
I PACK TO DECEIVE.

02:10.198 --> 02:11.799
WHAT DO YOU HAVE?
ELLEN'S TAX RETURNS.

02:11.832 --> 02:13.267
KEEP THE BUREAU
OUT OF IT?
YEAH.

02:13.301 --> 02:15.102
DIANA'S CONTACT AT THE IRS
CAME THROUGH.

02:15.135 --> 02:16.103
GOOD.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.605
WELL,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

02:17.638 --> 02:19.940
DID SHE HIDE THE EVIDENCE BOX
IN THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING?

02:19.973 --> 02:22.510
HER FIRST JOB AFTER WITSEC
THAT MOVED HER TO NEW YORK

02:22.543 --> 02:25.313
HAS THIS EMPLOYER I.D. NUMBER
HERE -- GRIFFIN-MOORE.

02:25.346 --> 02:26.614
PRIVATE SECURITY FIRM.

02:26.647 --> 02:27.981
PERFECT WAY
TO SATISFY HER INNER COP.

02:28.015 --> 02:28.982
UH-HUH.

02:29.016 --> 02:30.184
AND ONE OF THEIR CLIENTS

02:30.218 --> 02:31.519
WAS A TECH STARTUP
IN THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

02:31.552 --> 02:32.620
THAT'S GOT TO BE IT.

02:32.653 --> 02:34.622
WELL, THE QUESTION IS,
HOW DO WE SEARCH IT?

02:34.655 --> 02:37.625
WE DON'T. WE KEEP OUR
DISTANCE AND LET NEAL
SEARCH ON HIS OWN.

02:37.658 --> 02:38.959
DOES HE KNOW
WHERE TO LOOK?

02:38.992 --> 02:40.294
HE WILL.

02:40.328 --> 02:42.530
ALL RIGHT, I NEED YOU AND DIANA
TO KEEP AN EYE ON NEAL.

02:42.563 --> 02:43.631
NEAL
WHILE YOU'RE GONE.

02:43.664 --> 02:44.798
WE ALWAYS DO.

02:44.832 --> 02:46.834
BETWEEN THE CAR ACCIDENT
AND EVERYTHING ELSE,

02:46.867 --> 02:48.469
EL AND I
REALLY NEED TO GET AWAY.

02:48.502 --> 02:50.371
NO, I UNDERSTAND.
THANKS.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.473
HONEY?
YOUR PHONE JUST BUZZED.

02:52.506 --> 02:55.543
MIGHT BE THE HOTEL.
DO YOU REMEMBER THE AREA CODE?

02:55.576 --> 02:56.844
MY PHONE'S ON ME,
HON.

02:56.877 --> 02:58.145
BUT NICE TRY.

02:58.178 --> 03:01.215
SHE STILL HASN'T FIGURED OUT
WHERE YOU GUYS ARE GOING, HUH?

03:01.249 --> 03:02.516
NO, SHE HASN'T,

03:02.550 --> 03:04.552
BUT SHE'S CONDUCTING
A VERY THOROUGH INVESTIGATION.

03:04.585 --> 03:05.686
I'M SURE SHE IS.

03:09.857 --> 03:12.159
Sara:
AND THEN THIS IS IT.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.362
Neal: WOW.
LOOK AT THAT.

03:14.395 --> 03:15.729
I CAN SEE WHY
YOU WANTED MY HELP.

03:15.763 --> 03:16.697
DO YOU LOVE IT?
I DO.

03:16.730 --> 03:18.031
Peter: HELLO.
Elizabeth:
HI.

03:18.065 --> 03:19.367
Neal: HEY.

03:19.400 --> 03:21.869
YOU TWO READY TO KICK OFF
YOUR ROMANTIC WEEKEND?
YES.

03:21.902 --> 03:24.238
SHE DOESN'T KNOW WHERE WE'RE
GOING, SO NOBODY SAY ANYTHING.

03:24.272 --> 03:25.239
OKAY.

03:25.273 --> 03:26.507
IS IT SAFE
TO MENTION THE EARRINGS?

03:26.540 --> 03:28.409
ARE THOSE EMERALDS?
THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

03:28.442 --> 03:30.411
WELL, THANK YOU.
THEY WERE MY GRANDMOTHER'S.

03:30.444 --> 03:31.512
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

03:31.545 --> 03:33.013
OH, SPEAKING OF
BEAUTIFUL...

03:33.046 --> 03:34.214
Elizabeth:
OH, MY GOSH.

03:34.248 --> 03:35.749
FROM MARIE ANTOINETTE'S
BEDROOM IN VERSAILLES.

03:35.783 --> 03:36.850
[ GASPS ]

03:36.884 --> 03:38.386
DOES IT
SMELL LIKE CAKE?

03:39.953 --> 03:41.088
CAKE. WHAT?

03:41.121 --> 03:42.390
OH, NOTHING.

03:43.591 --> 03:45.426
I'M GONNA CHECK IN
ON THE STAFF.

03:45.459 --> 03:47.060
I'LL TAKE YOU BACK.
GREAT.

03:48.629 --> 03:51.732
SO...YOU AND SARA?

03:51.765 --> 03:53.534
DEDUCE THAT
ALL BY YOURSELF?
I DID.

03:53.567 --> 03:56.036
SHOULDN'T YOU BE LEAVING
FOR YOUR BED-AND-BREAKFAST SOON?

03:56.069 --> 03:58.205
ENOUGH. REMEMBER,
I'M ONLY TO BE DISTURBED --

03:58.238 --> 03:59.740
IF SOMEONE DIES.
I KNOW THE DRILL.

03:59.773 --> 04:00.774
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

04:02.910 --> 04:05.112
OH,
THE RUSTY EGRET.

04:05.145 --> 04:06.246
YEAH.

04:06.280 --> 04:08.248
MUST BE CHECKING IN
FOR OUR CONFIRMATION.

04:08.282 --> 04:09.817
HELLO?

04:10.951 --> 04:12.953
[ SIGHS ] WELL,
EVERYTHING'S UNDER CONTROL.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.054
GOOD.

04:14.087 --> 04:15.289
NOW YOU TWO
CAN RELAX THIS WEEKEND.

04:15.323 --> 04:16.557
I HOPE YOU CAN, TOO.

04:16.590 --> 04:18.058
ME?
DON'T PLAY INNOCENT.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.593
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN
DEALING WITH A LOT,

04:19.627 --> 04:22.262
AND ME ASKING YOU TO LIE
TO PETER ONLY ADDED TO IT.

04:22.296 --> 04:24.798
I UNDERSTAND WHY YOU WANT
TO KEEP HIM OUT OF THIS.

04:24.832 --> 04:26.099
I JUST WANT HIM SAFE.

04:26.133 --> 04:28.569
NO ARGUMENT HERE.
KEEP HIM FAR AWAY.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.738
Peter: WELL,
OUR CHECK-IN IS CONFIRMED,

04:30.771 --> 04:33.240
BUT OUR DOG-SITTER
JUST CANCELED.

04:33.273 --> 04:34.442
OH.
LET'S CALL THE BERMANS.
BUSY.

04:34.475 --> 04:35.576
I'LL WATCH SATCHMO.

04:35.609 --> 04:36.610
WHAT? NO.

04:36.644 --> 04:38.779
WHAT? YOU DON'T TRUST ME
WITH YOUR DOG?

04:38.812 --> 04:40.247
I DON'T TRUST YOU
WITH MY HOUSE.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.149
ALL RIGHT, I CAN BRING SATCHMO
OVER TO MY PLACE.

04:42.182 --> 04:44.084
PERFECT.
A VACATION FOR SATCHMO.

04:44.117 --> 04:45.152
[ SIGHS ]

04:45.185 --> 04:46.654
ALL RIGHT.
HERE.

04:46.687 --> 04:47.921
OH, NO NEED.

04:47.955 --> 04:50.090
I'LL USE THE ONE IN THE FAKE
ROCK IN YOUR FLOWER BED.

04:50.123 --> 04:52.426
[ LAUGHS ]

04:52.460 --> 04:53.761
INSTRUCTIONS
ARE ON THE TABLE.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.096
OUR VALUABLES ARE INVENTORIED,
AND THE SECOND WE'RE BACK,

04:56.129 --> 04:58.265
WE'RE CHANGING THE LOCKS
AND RESETTING THE ALARM CODES.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.600
I WOULD EXPECT
NOTHING LESS.

04:59.633 --> 05:00.801
AND MAYBE
SARA COULD DROP BY

05:00.834 --> 05:03.136
AND CHECK IN ON SATCHMO,
AS WELL?
HMM, WHAT?

05:04.037 --> 05:05.439
SURE.

05:05.473 --> 05:07.274
YEAH, SURE.
WHY NOT?

05:07.307 --> 05:09.109
YES,
OF COURSE.
YEAH.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.444
GO.

05:10.478 --> 05:11.779
GO, HAVE A GREAT WEEKEND.
COME ON.

05:11.812 --> 05:14.815
Neal: SATCHMO'S IN GOOD HANDS.
HE'S COVERED.

05:14.848 --> 05:17.451
THEY KNOW.
YEAH, THEY KNOW.

05:17.485 --> 05:19.787
HEY, LISTEN, CAN WE GO BY
THAT NEW COFFEE SHOP?

05:19.820 --> 05:21.288
I WANT TO GET
AN ICED LATTE.

05:21.321 --> 05:22.990
UNLESS WE'RE GOING
SOMEPLACE COLD.

05:23.023 --> 05:24.024
GET THE ICE.

05:24.057 --> 05:26.293
I'LL GET
THE HOT CHOCOLATE.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.028
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:28.061 --> 05:30.130
Sara: SO, THIS IS
THE SECURITY SETUP.

05:30.163 --> 05:32.533
IT'S FAIRLY SIMPLE,
BUT IT SHOULD DO THE TRICK.

05:32.566 --> 05:33.701
NICE FIELD OF VISION.

05:33.734 --> 05:36.970
DECENT LUX PARAMETER.

05:37.004 --> 05:38.839
I ONLY SEE ONE PROBLEM.
HMM?

05:38.872 --> 05:40.173
YOU'RE BEING ROBBED.
WHAT?

05:40.207 --> 05:42.376
LOOK.
[ GASPS ]

05:42.410 --> 05:43.811
EVERYBODY, BE COOL!

05:43.844 --> 05:45.045
THIS IS A ROBBERY.

05:45.078 --> 05:48.048
DO AS WE SAY,
AND NO ONE WILL GET HURT.

05:48.081 --> 05:49.983
YOU, GET OVER HERE.
GET DOWN.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.184
HEY, YOU, BIG BOY,

05:51.218 --> 05:55.222
HAND YOUR PIECE OVER
TO THE LADY NICE AND EASY.

05:56.590 --> 05:58.158
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
EYES TO THE FLOOR.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.326
[ Laughing ] OH.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.328
NO HEROES TODAY,
FOLKS.

06:01.361 --> 06:02.663
BABE,
I CAN'T GET IT.

06:02.696 --> 06:03.864
OH, GOD.

06:03.897 --> 06:05.065
YEAH, YOU GOT IT BABE.
YOU GOT IT. JUST HIT IT.

06:05.098 --> 06:06.500
SHE'S GONNA BE UPSET
IF SHE DOESN'T GET THAT PERFUME.

06:06.534 --> 06:08.068
NOT AS UPSET
AS HER BOYFRIEND.

06:08.101 --> 06:10.571
EVERYBODY STAY DOWN
OR YOU'RE GONNA EAT A BULLET!

06:10.604 --> 06:11.705
HE'S GONNA
KILL SOMEBODY.

06:11.739 --> 06:13.006
SARA, WAIT!

06:13.040 --> 06:16.176
I LEAVE FOR TWO MINUTES,
AND IT'S A COSTUME PARTY?

06:16.209 --> 06:18.345
SHUT YOUR MOUTH
AND GET ON THE FLOOR.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.514
DOWN!
SARA,
DO WHAT HE SAYS.

06:20.548 --> 06:23.083
[ LAUGHS ] WHAT DOES SHE THINK
SHE'S GONNA DO WITH THAT?

06:24.284 --> 06:25.252
GET OUT.

06:25.285 --> 06:26.754
ATTITUDE LIKE THAT
WILL GET YOU

06:26.787 --> 06:28.422
SOME SERIOUS TIME
IN THE COTTAGE, HONEY.

06:28.456 --> 06:30.190
Penny:
OH, MY GOD.
LET'S GO.

06:30.223 --> 06:32.025
THANK YOU,
EVERYBODY.

06:32.059 --> 06:33.427
[ LAUGHS ]

06:40.968 --> 06:42.603
WE'RE BLOCKED IN.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.104
YOU'RE
SUCH A GENTLEMAN.

06:44.137 --> 06:45.773
FOR YOU, MY DEAR,
ANYTHING.

06:46.574 --> 06:47.775
DAMN VAN.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.610
THIS WAY.

06:53.113 --> 06:55.048
[ WHISTLES ]
HEY.

06:55.082 --> 06:56.049
GIVE US THE KEYS.

06:56.083 --> 06:57.217
MY WIFE
IS IN THE CAR.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.385
I DON'T CARE.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.888
YOU'RE MAKING
A VERY BIG MISTAKE RIGHT NOW.

07:00.921 --> 07:02.089
IT'S HUGE.

07:02.122 --> 07:05.258
ONE MORE WORD
AND SOMEBODY GETS HURT.

07:06.660 --> 07:07.795
COME ON.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.735
THAT'S RIGHT.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.269
GET IN.

07:16.303 --> 07:18.071
BABY,
WE DON'T NEED THEM.

07:18.105 --> 07:20.808
THEY SAW OUR FACES.
DRIVE. GET IN.

07:24.978 --> 07:27.247
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

07:27.280 --> 07:28.516
WAS THIS
A PART OF THE SURPRISE?

07:50.003 --> 07:52.305
Peter: WHAT IS THIS?
SOME KIND OF SUBSTATION?

07:52.339 --> 07:56.877
Oz: ABANDONED BY THE CITY.
IT'S OURS NOW. MOVE!

08:01.048 --> 08:03.283
I'M ONLY GONNA SAY THIS
ONE MORE TIME.

08:03.316 --> 08:04.852
MY WIFE, ELIZABETH,
AND I

08:04.885 --> 08:07.187
WERE LEAVING TOWN
FOR A GETAWAY WEEKEND.

08:07.220 --> 08:08.956
THAT'S ALL --
SHUT UP!

08:08.989 --> 08:10.524
EMPTY YOUR POCKETS.

08:10.558 --> 08:11.559
DO IT!

08:16.664 --> 08:21.034
PETER AND ELIZABETH BURKE,
WARREN STREET, COBBLE HILL,

08:21.068 --> 08:22.636
JUST LIKE
THEY SAID.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.638
OZ,
WE ARE NOT KIDNAPPERS.

08:24.672 --> 08:26.206
Peter:
LISTEN TO HER.

08:26.239 --> 08:28.642
YOU LET US GO NOW,
YOU'RE LOOKING AT ARMED ROBBERY.

08:28.676 --> 08:29.877
BUT IF YOU
KEEP US HERE,

08:29.910 --> 08:31.645
YOU'RE PLAYING
IN A WHOLE NEW BALLPARK.

08:31.679 --> 08:33.146
YOU WATCH TOO MUCH
"LAW & ORDER."

08:33.180 --> 08:35.482
WE LET THEM GO, AND THEY GO
STRAIGHT TO THE COPS.

08:35.515 --> 08:36.550
JUST LET US WALK.

08:36.584 --> 08:38.318
WE -- WE PROMISE --
WE'RE NOT GONNA --

08:38.351 --> 08:39.720
YOU'LL WHAT?
DUMMY UP?

08:39.753 --> 08:41.655
WE LOOK LIKE
AMATEURS TO YOU?!

08:41.689 --> 08:42.823
Penny:
S-S-STOP!

08:42.856 --> 08:46.359
OKAY, WE JUST NEED
A SECOND TO FIGURE THIS OUT.

08:46.393 --> 08:49.529
BABY,
YOU NEED TO RELAX, OKAY?

08:49.563 --> 08:53.867
YEAH. YEAH.
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

08:53.901 --> 08:56.570
WE'LL JUST MAKE SURE
OUR FISH DON'T SWIM.

09:09.917 --> 09:11.184
Neal: THOUGHT
THEY WERE BONNIE AND CLYDE.

09:11.218 --> 09:12.252
THEY CAME IN
WITH THESE MASKS --

09:12.285 --> 09:13.687
Jones: WE OFFICIALLY
HAVE OURSELVES A NEW CASE.

09:13.721 --> 09:15.689
Both: NATE "OZ" --

09:15.723 --> 09:17.591
OH, YOU GO AHEAD.
OH, NO, LADIES FIRST.

09:17.625 --> 09:19.860
WHY NOT GUYS FIRST?
OKAY.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.095
NATE "OZ" --
NATE "OZ" OSBOURNE
WAS SERVING A 15-YEAR SENTENCE

09:22.129 --> 09:23.697
FOR ASSAULTING
A POLICE OFFICER

09:23.731 --> 09:25.866
WHEN HE ESCAPED
HUDSON CORRECTIONAL LAST WEEK.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.601
WE CROSS-REFERENCED CAFFREY'S
PHYSICAL DESCRIPTION --

09:27.635 --> 09:29.202
THANK YOU, CAFFREY --

09:29.236 --> 09:30.738
AGAINST FORMER HUDSON INMATES,
AND WE GOT OUR GUY.

09:30.771 --> 09:32.039
OSBOURNE
AND HIS LADY FRIEND

09:32.072 --> 09:33.607
ABANDONED THEIR GETAWAY CAR
AT THE SCENE.

09:33.641 --> 09:36.043
NYPD CORDONED THE AREA,
BUT SO FAR, NO TRACE.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.378
THE PERFUME WASN'T
THEIR FIRST TARGET, EITHER.

09:38.411 --> 09:41.414
THEIR M.O. MATCHES A THEFT
FROM WEATHERBY'S TWO DAYS AGO --

09:41.448 --> 09:43.884
THE WEDDING RING JOE DiMAGGIO
GAVE MARILYN MONROE.

09:43.917 --> 09:45.919
IT MADE ITS WAY ON TO THE FINGER
OF OSBOURNE'S BETTER HALF.

09:45.953 --> 09:48.756
WELL, NOTHING SAYS COMMITMENT
LIKE A STOLEN WEDDING RING.

09:48.789 --> 09:49.757
ANY INFORMATION ON THE GIRL?

09:49.790 --> 09:50.791
NOT MUCH.

09:50.824 --> 09:52.059
WE GOT HER PRINTS
OFF THE GUARD'S GUN,

09:52.092 --> 09:53.093
BUT NO CRIMINAL RECORD.

09:53.126 --> 09:54.762
THEY LEFT
THE GUARD'S GUN BEHIND?

09:54.795 --> 09:56.563
SHE DROPPED IT
IN A CHAMPAGNE BUCKET.

09:56.596 --> 10:00.433
COULD I SEE THE BALLISTICS
REPORT FROM THE SHOT OZ FIRED?

10:00.467 --> 10:02.402
KID'S BARELY
OLD ENOUGH TO VOTE,

10:02.435 --> 10:04.437
AND HE THINKS
HE CAN THREATEN YOU?

10:04.471 --> 10:06.473
THE SECOND
I GET YOU OUT OF HERE...

10:06.506 --> 10:07.574
HE'S IN
OVER HIS HEAD.

10:07.607 --> 10:08.642
WAY OVER.

10:08.676 --> 10:10.243
I DON'T THINK
THEY WANT TO HURT US.

10:10.277 --> 10:11.578
Peter: MAYBE NOT HER,
BUT HIM?

10:11.611 --> 10:13.446
"DUMMY UP" AND "FISH"
ARE PRISON SLANG.

10:13.480 --> 10:14.481
HE'S DONE TIME.

10:14.514 --> 10:16.149
OR WATCHED
A LOT OF TV.

10:16.183 --> 10:17.484
SHUT UP DOWN THERE!

10:21.955 --> 10:24.491
SHE'S
A CALMING INFLUENCE.

10:24.524 --> 10:25.926
MAYBE
IF I TALK TO HER,

10:25.959 --> 10:27.828
APPEAL TO HER
ON A PERSONAL LEVEL.

10:27.861 --> 10:29.129
I DON'T KNOW.

10:29.162 --> 10:30.764
I HAVE
DONE THIS BEFORE.

10:30.798 --> 10:32.265
THAT MAKES
TWO OF US.

10:32.299 --> 10:35.102
WELL, AT LEAST THIS TIME,
WE GET TO BE TIED UP TOGETHER.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.436
Oz: GOOD NEWS.

10:36.469 --> 10:40.607
WITH A SLIGHT ADJUSTMENT,
OUR THIRD ACT IS BACK ON TRACK.

10:40.640 --> 10:44.311
SO PENNY HERE IS GONNA BABYSIT
WHILE I TAKE CARE OF BUSINESS.

10:49.683 --> 10:50.617
BE SAFE.

10:50.650 --> 10:51.985
ALWAYS.

10:52.019 --> 10:54.121
IF YOU'RE DITCHING OUR CAR,
WE HAVE BAGS IN THE TRUNK.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.823
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
I'M DITCHING YOUR CAR?

10:55.856 --> 10:58.625
ALL THAT "LAW & ORDER"
I WATCH.

10:58.658 --> 11:00.460
Elizabeth: IF WE'RE GONNA
BE HERE FOR A WHILE,

11:00.493 --> 11:01.862
IT'D BE NICE
TO CHANGE OUR CLOTHES.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.664
EH?

11:07.334 --> 11:09.202
"CHANGE OUR CLOTHES."

11:09.236 --> 11:10.670
COBBLE HILL.

11:19.412 --> 11:21.648
HOW LONG HAVE YOU TWO
BEEN MARRIED?

11:21.681 --> 11:22.649
[ PENNY LAUGHS ]

11:22.682 --> 11:25.152
WE HAVE A LOVE
FOR THE AGES.

11:25.185 --> 11:27.154
I MEAN, WHY DO WE NEED
SOME STUPID CONTRACT

11:27.187 --> 11:28.722
TO TELL US
WHAT WE ALREADY KNOW?

11:28.756 --> 11:30.657
FOR STARTERS,
HEALTH INSURANCE,

11:30.690 --> 11:32.860
HOMEOWNERSHIP,
SHARED CELLPHONE PLANS.

11:32.893 --> 11:34.494
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:34.527 --> 11:37.865
UH, WHAT OZ AND I HAVE
IS MUCH BIGGER THAN ALL OF THAT.

11:37.898 --> 11:41.234
HE'S A REALLY GOOD GUY
WITH A REALLY, REALLY BIG HEART.

11:41.268 --> 11:43.336
YOU'LL UNDERSTAND
IF WE DON'T SEE HIM THAT WAY.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.739
WELL,
YOU DON'T KNOW HIM, SO...

11:45.773 --> 11:48.075
RIGHT.
HE IS GOOD.

11:48.108 --> 11:51.178
AND, SURE, HIS COUSIN TALKED HIM
INTO STEALING CAR PARTS,

11:51.211 --> 11:53.380
BUT THAT DOESN'T MAKE HIM
A BAD PERSON.

11:53.413 --> 11:55.916
YOU DON'T SERVE HARD TIME
FOR STEALING RIMS.

11:55.949 --> 11:57.751
WHAT HAPPENED?

11:57.785 --> 11:59.586
[ SIGHS ]

11:59.619 --> 12:01.254
IT WAS HIS FIRST TIME.

12:01.288 --> 12:02.355
THE POLICE SHOWED UP.

12:02.389 --> 12:04.191
WHEN THEY TOLD HIM
TO RAISE HIS HANDS,

12:04.224 --> 12:05.926
HE ACCIDENTALLY DROPPED
A BATTERY THAT HE WAS HOLDING

12:05.959 --> 12:06.927
ON THE COP'S FOOT.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.261
ACCIDENTALLY?

12:08.295 --> 12:10.764
WHAT ELSE WAS HE SUPPOSED TO DO
OTHER THAN DROP IT?

12:10.798 --> 12:12.432
I MEAN, THE GUY
HAD A GUN IN HIS FACE.

12:12.465 --> 12:14.267
THE OFFICER
DIDN'T SEE IT THAT WAY?
NO.

12:14.301 --> 12:15.735
THE COP LIED TO THE D.A.

12:15.769 --> 12:18.105
THEY CHARGED HIM WITH
ASSAULT ON A POLICE OFFICER.

12:18.138 --> 12:19.706
YOU CAN GET
15 YEARS FOR THAT.

12:19.739 --> 12:21.574
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT THE JUDGE GAVE HIM.

12:21.608 --> 12:22.575
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:22.609 --> 12:23.911
I MEAN,
HE DIDN'T DESERVE THAT.

12:23.944 --> 12:26.079
SO HE WAS RELEASED EARLY
ON GOOD BEHAVIOR.

12:27.781 --> 12:28.748
NO.

12:28.782 --> 12:31.251
HE ESCAPED,
AND YOU HELPED HIM.

12:31.284 --> 12:34.054
THE COP LIED.
THE JUDGE WOULDN'T LISTEN.

12:34.087 --> 12:35.255
WHAT ELSE
WERE WE SUPPOSED TO DO?

12:35.288 --> 12:36.423
I MEAN,
THE SYSTEM FAILED HIM.

12:36.456 --> 12:37.757
ALL WE HAVE IS EACH OTHER.

12:37.791 --> 12:40.227
I MEAN, I'M SURE THERE ARE
A TON OF PEOPLE OUT THERE

12:40.260 --> 12:42.429
WHO ARE WORRIED ABOUT
THE TWO OF YOU RIGHT NOW.

12:42.462 --> 12:44.932
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

12:44.965 --> 12:47.300
UH, THIS IS ESTHER
FROM THE RUSTY EGRET.

12:47.334 --> 12:50.737
I THOUGHT WE WERE CONFIRMED
YOU'D BE HERE BY NOON,

12:50.770 --> 12:52.272
AND IT'S ALMOST 3:00.

12:52.305 --> 12:54.975
I'LL TRY YOUR CELL AGAIN.
[ ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS ]

12:57.344 --> 13:00.080
WAIT. THE SUIT ACTUALLY
GAVE YOU ACCESS TO HIS HOUSE?

13:00.113 --> 13:01.148
YES, MOZ.

13:01.181 --> 13:03.416
UNWISE. WE SHOULD
TEACH HIM A LESSON.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.618
I'M THINKING MICRO CAM
IN A LAMPSHADE.

13:05.652 --> 13:07.754
HE'LL FIND IT, OF COURSE,
BUT THAT'S THE POINT.

13:07.787 --> 13:10.090
WE'RE PICKING UP SATCHMO
AND WE'RE LEAVING, ALL RIGHT?

13:10.123 --> 13:11.158
FINE.

13:11.191 --> 13:14.094
I DON'T SEE WHY
YOU'D WANT TO PASS UP

13:14.127 --> 13:17.597
A PRIME OPPORTUNITY
SUCH AS THIS, BUT WHATEVER.

13:17.630 --> 13:19.466
WHOA! SERIOUSLY?
BOXED WINE?

13:19.499 --> 13:21.101
WE GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

13:21.134 --> 13:22.836
YOU MIND PICKING UP
SATCHMO'S WATER BOWL?

13:22.870 --> 13:24.471
IT'S OVER
BY THE DESK.

13:24.504 --> 13:27.207
AND NO SNOOPING.
UH-HUH.

13:29.009 --> 13:31.144
WHOA, THE SUIT LEFT
ELLEN'S IRS FORMS

13:31.178 --> 13:33.113
OUT HERE
FOR ANYONE TO SEE.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.514
HEY. NO.
I SAID NO.

13:34.547 --> 13:37.484
THEY'RE FROM WHEN
WITSEC MOVED HER TO NEW YORK.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.154
WELL, ANY INSIGHT
INTO HER LIFE FROM THAT TIME

13:41.188 --> 13:43.290
COULD HELP US ISOLATE
WHERE SHE HID THE EVIDENCE.

13:43.323 --> 13:44.624
IT'S A LONG SHOT.

13:44.657 --> 13:47.660
SO IS BLINDLY SEARCHING A
2-MILLION-SQUARE-FOOT BUILDING.

13:47.694 --> 13:52.465
EXCELLENT POINT.
HERE. ALLOW ME.

13:52.499 --> 13:54.634
OKAY.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.203
YOU KNOW, IT'S NOT TOO LATE
TO HIDE THAT MICRO CAM --

13:56.236 --> 13:57.637
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.
OKAY.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.473
NEXT.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.809
NEXT.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.812
JESUS, BABY,
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

14:05.845 --> 14:09.049
[ LAUGHS ] WELL, I ACQUIRED US
A NEW VEHICLE

14:09.082 --> 14:11.985
AND I FINISHED UP RECON
FOR OUR THIRD ACT.

14:12.019 --> 14:13.820
AND YOU WENT
TO GRISTEDES?

14:13.853 --> 14:15.488
YEAH. WELL, WE GOT
A BIG DAY TOMORROW.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.490
CAN'T DO IT
ON AN EMPTY STOMACH.

14:17.524 --> 14:18.525
YOU ARE TOO GOOD,
BABY.

14:18.558 --> 14:19.726
[ OZ CHUCKLES ]

14:19.759 --> 14:22.062
YOU HAVE TO ADMIT --
THEY ARE KIND OF SWEET TOGETHER.

14:22.095 --> 14:24.197
I HOPE THAT'S
THE STOCKHOLM SYNDROME TALKING.

14:24.231 --> 14:26.499
BURKES OF COBBLE HILL,
KEEP UP THE GOOD BEHAVIOR,

14:26.533 --> 14:28.068
THERE MIGHT BE
SOME OF MY FAMOUS

14:28.101 --> 14:29.769
CHOW-HALL CASSEROLE
IN IT FOR YOU.

14:30.737 --> 14:32.505
HUH?

14:32.539 --> 14:34.674
YOU SURE
THEY DIDN'T GIVE YOU TROUBLE?
Penny: SURE.

14:34.707 --> 14:35.742
HEY, HON.

14:35.775 --> 14:37.177
I SEE IT.

14:37.210 --> 14:39.212
THE SECOND THEY REALIZE THEY'VE
KIDNAPPED A FEDERAL AGENT,

14:39.246 --> 14:40.380
ALL BETS ARE OFF.

14:41.381 --> 14:42.415
YOU PACKED YOUR GUN.

14:42.449 --> 14:44.184
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN GET TO IT?

14:44.217 --> 14:45.252
NOT WITHOUT HELP.

14:45.285 --> 14:47.554
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO DO THIS TOGETHER.

15:01.601 --> 15:04.104
THERE IS STILL A CHANCE THAT
WE CAN GET THE ATOMIZER BACK

15:04.137 --> 15:05.572
BEFORE THE EVENT
TOMORROW, RIGHT?

15:05.605 --> 15:06.706
YEAH, WE'RE ON IT.
OKAY.

15:06.739 --> 15:07.707
YOU OKAY?

15:07.740 --> 15:09.876
Diana: BALLISTICS
IS STILL ON SCENE,

15:09.909 --> 15:11.278
BUT WE GOT A HIT
ON OSBOURNE'S SIDEKICK.

15:11.311 --> 15:12.946
Jones: I HAD
HUDSON CORRECTIONAL

15:12.980 --> 15:14.948
PULL HIS CORRESPONDENCE
AND VISITOR LOGS.

15:14.982 --> 15:16.383
Sara:
SO WE'VE GOT A NAME.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.051
YEAH, PENNY CHASE.

15:18.085 --> 15:19.386
CLEAN RECORD.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.721
SHE WORKS AS A COPY EDITOR
FOR A BOOK PUBLISHER

15:21.754 --> 15:23.723
SPECIALIZING
IN PAPERBACK ROMANCE NOVELS.

15:23.756 --> 15:25.558
WHAT IS HER CONNECTION
TO OSBOURNE?

15:25.592 --> 15:27.260
PRISON PEN PALS
TURNED SOUL MATES.

15:27.294 --> 15:29.296
COPIES OF THE PRISON LETTERS
RIGHT HERE.

15:29.329 --> 15:30.964
THEY MET
WHILE HE WAS IN PRISON?

15:30.998 --> 15:32.565
Diana:
AND IT WASN'T BY CHANCE.

15:32.599 --> 15:34.801
PENNY WAS A LONGTIME SUBSCRIBER
TO MUGSHOT MONTHLY.

15:34.834 --> 15:37.104
APPARENTLY, SHE LIKED
OSBOURNE'S MUG AND WROTE HIM.

15:37.137 --> 15:38.938
THEIR RELATIONSHIP
TOOK OFF FROM THERE.

15:38.972 --> 15:40.240
THIS IS NOT
A REAL MAGAZINE.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.275
OH, YEAH. WOMEN WHO FALL
FOR INMATES -- IT'S A THING.

15:42.309 --> 15:43.776
THEY'RE CALLED
PRISON BUNNIES.

15:43.810 --> 15:45.412
OH, GOD.
THE WEIRD GETS WEIRDER.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.248
SAYS THE ONLY WOMAN IN THE ROOM
WHO'S ACTUALLY DATED AN INMATE.

15:48.281 --> 15:51.651
HEY.
IT IS NOT THE SAME.
NEAL.

15:51.684 --> 15:53.753
WAIT. ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH THIS PHENOMENON?

15:53.786 --> 15:57.424
DURING MY PRISON STAY,
I MAY HAVE HAD A FEW ADMIRERS.

15:57.457 --> 15:58.992
Jones:
MORE LIKE A FEW HUNDRED.

15:59.026 --> 16:00.660
BUT DIDN'T YOU RESPOND
WITH A FORM LETTER?

16:00.693 --> 16:01.928
ONLY AFTER
THE CARPAL TUNNEL.

16:01.961 --> 16:02.829
OH.

16:02.862 --> 16:04.264
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

16:04.297 --> 16:05.498
I LET THEM DOWN EASY.

16:05.532 --> 16:06.599
RIGHT. LET'S GET BACK
TO THE CASE, HUH?

16:06.633 --> 16:08.501
I SKIMMED
A FEW OF THEIR LETTERS.

16:08.535 --> 16:10.937
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE
THEY THINK THEY'RE CHARACTERS

16:10.970 --> 16:12.772
IN SOME GREAT LOVE STORY
OR SOMETHING.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.107
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

16:14.141 --> 16:16.276
OSBOURNE PROMISES
TO MAKE HER AN HONEST WOMAN

16:16.309 --> 16:17.510
AFTER HIS RELEASE.

16:17.544 --> 16:19.446
I MEAN, IT'S POSSIBLE
HE LURED HER INTO THIS.

16:19.479 --> 16:21.781
WELL, HE MADE HER AN HONEST
WOMAN BY GETTING HER A RING.

16:21.814 --> 16:24.451
HE KEPT HIS PROMISE.

16:24.484 --> 16:25.785
IF HE MADE HER
ANY OTHER PROMISES,

16:25.818 --> 16:27.287
IT MIGHT LEAD US
TO THEIR NEXT TARGET.

16:27.320 --> 16:28.321
ARE THESE
ALL THE LETTERS?

16:28.355 --> 16:30.123
Diana:
THERE'S ABOUT 700.

16:30.157 --> 16:31.791
OOH. ALL RIGHT.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.326
LET'S GET STARTED.

16:43.503 --> 16:44.671
Elizabeth:
OH, NO, NO.

16:44.704 --> 16:47.640
D-DON'T ADD
THE ONIONS RAW LIKE THAT.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.709
YOU SHOULD SAUTé THEM.
THEY'RE MUCH SWEETER THAT WAY.

16:49.742 --> 16:50.810
Oz: FINE.

16:50.843 --> 16:52.645
WHAT DO I DO?

16:52.679 --> 16:58.218
WELL, Y-YOU GET A SAUTé PAN,
AND YOU HEAT UP SOME BUTTER.

16:59.886 --> 17:01.088
THE SILVER ONE.

17:06.093 --> 17:09.829
OH, THAT'S...
WAY TOO MUCH BUTTER.

17:09.862 --> 17:12.232
YOU WANT TO COME IN HERE
AND DO THIS?

17:12.265 --> 17:15.868
WELL, I DO SORT OF
RUN A CATERING COMPANY.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.940
[ CLICK ]

17:31.618 --> 17:33.086
MAY I DO THAT?

17:33.120 --> 17:34.187
I DON'T THINK SO.

17:34.221 --> 17:35.922
YOU DO HAVE A GUN.

17:35.955 --> 17:38.558
[ KNIFE CLATTERS ]

17:44.564 --> 17:46.399
IT'S THE PROPER KNIFE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:55.074 --> 17:58.611
DAMN, LIZZY BURKE,
YOU GOT SOME SKILLS.

17:59.612 --> 18:02.249
YOU KNOW, HARRIET VAN HORNE
SAID IT BEST.

18:02.282 --> 18:04.083
COOKING
IS LIKE LOVE.

18:04.117 --> 18:06.386
YOU EITHER APPROACH IT
WITH ABANDON OR NOT AT ALL.

18:06.419 --> 18:07.754
LOVE AND ABANDON.

18:07.787 --> 18:09.722
KIND OF DIG THAT.
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT.

18:09.756 --> 18:11.758
THE FIRST TIME I MADE THIS
FOR PENNY,

18:11.791 --> 18:13.760
SHE SAID I COOKED BETTER
THAN HER OWN MOTHER.

18:13.793 --> 18:15.728
[ SIGHS ]
Oz: SHE WAS LYING
THROUGH HER TEETH.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.930
BUT IT WAS REALLY CUTE.
[ LAUGHS ]

18:17.964 --> 18:19.566
SO, WHERE
WERE YOU GONNA TAKE HER?

18:19.599 --> 18:23.102
TO A BED-AND-BREAKFAST
IN THE GREEN MOUNTAINS.

18:23.136 --> 18:26.072
NOTHING BUT NATURE,
MY BEAUTIFUL WIFE,

18:26.105 --> 18:28.608
AND A COUPLE
OF GOOD CRIME NOVELS.

18:28.641 --> 18:29.809
WOULD HAVE
BEEN AMAZING.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.411
NO, SERIOUSLY, LIKE...

18:31.444 --> 18:33.746
WHERE WERE YOU
GONNA TAKE HER?

18:33.780 --> 18:35.081
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'VE KIDNAPPED ME.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.649
YOU DON'T GET
TO JUDGE ME.

18:36.683 --> 18:38.918
COME ON, DON'T YOU THINK
THAT SOUNDS BORING AS HELL?

18:38.951 --> 18:41.087
NO, I THINK IT SOUNDS
RELAXING AS HELL.

18:41.120 --> 18:42.455
DIFFERENT STROKES,
I GUESS.

18:42.489 --> 18:45.958
I MEAN, THE PART
ABOUT THE BOOK SOUNDS OKAY.

18:45.992 --> 18:47.794
I LIKE ROMANCE NOVELS.

18:47.827 --> 18:49.929
BUT TRUE CRIME
IS GOOD, TOO.

18:49.962 --> 18:52.599
MOST OF THEM
DON'T HAVE HAPPY ENDINGS.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.434
NO,
BUT THE ROMANCE BOOKS DO.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.469
THAT'S WHY
I LIKE READING THEM.

18:56.503 --> 18:57.770
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:57.804 --> 19:01.608
SO, THAT'S HOW I GOT THE IDEA
TO START THE...OOH.

19:01.641 --> 19:02.975
Oz: YOU OKAY?

19:03.009 --> 19:05.011
YEAH, I THINK I JUST GOT
SOME GARLIC POWDER IN MY EYE.

19:05.044 --> 19:06.946
YOU WANT TO WASH IT OUT
OR SOMETHING?

19:06.979 --> 19:10.350
UM...ACTUALLY, UH, I THINK
I HAVE SOME EYE DROPS IN MY BAG.

19:10.383 --> 19:12.952
HEY, PEN,
YOU HELP LIZZY OUT WITH HER BAG?

19:12.985 --> 19:14.954
YEAH.

19:14.987 --> 19:16.789
THANKS.
[ GRUNTS ]

19:16.823 --> 19:19.158
SHOULD BE RIGHT ON TOP
IN THE TOILETRY BAG.

19:23.230 --> 19:25.031
PERFECT.
[ GASPS ]

19:25.064 --> 19:27.166
OH,
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL!

19:27.200 --> 19:29.969
IT'S A CLASSIC
VON FURSTENBERG.

19:30.002 --> 19:31.971
YOU SHOULD
TRY IT ON.

19:32.004 --> 19:32.972
REALLY?

19:33.005 --> 19:35.842
THERE'S SOME SHOES
IN THERE, TOO.

19:36.843 --> 19:38.878
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:38.911 --> 19:40.880
OH. I WASN'T SURE
HOW TO PACK.

19:42.915 --> 19:43.883
[ LAUGHS ]

19:43.916 --> 19:45.818
PETER, HEY, UH,
THREE THINGS --

19:45.852 --> 19:47.820
NOBODY'S DEAD,
SATCHMO'S FINE,

19:47.854 --> 19:48.988
AND I CHANGED
YOUR ALARM CODE,

19:49.021 --> 19:50.357
WHICH I'LL GLADLY
GIVE BACK TO YOU

19:50.390 --> 19:52.892
IN EXCHANGE FOR
SOME MAPLE SYRUP.

19:52.925 --> 19:54.361
TELL ELIZABETH
I SAY HI.

19:54.394 --> 19:55.362
HOW ARE THE BURKES?

19:55.395 --> 19:56.729
MAINTAINING RADIO SILENCE,
AS PROMISED.

19:56.763 --> 19:58.398
I'M JUST CALLING
TO LET THEM KNOW

19:58.431 --> 20:00.166
IT'S ALL QUIET
ON THE SATCHMO FRONT.

20:00.199 --> 20:01.067
YOU FIND SOMETHING?

20:01.100 --> 20:02.569
YEAH, TOO BAD
PETER'S NOT HERE.

20:02.602 --> 20:04.003
HE'D LOVE THIS.

20:04.036 --> 20:07.707
LAST AUGUST, OZ PROMISED PENNY
TO TREAT HER LIKE A QUEEN.

20:09.041 --> 20:10.677
THE MARIE ANTOINETTE
PERFUME BOTTLE.

20:10.710 --> 20:11.678
WE WERE RIGHT.

20:11.711 --> 20:13.513
HE'S STEALING
TO FULFILL A PROMISE.

20:13.546 --> 20:15.548
RIGHT, AND I MIGHT THINK
IT WAS ADORABLE

20:15.582 --> 20:17.250
IF THEY DIDN'T SNATCH
MY PERFUME.

20:17.284 --> 20:18.751
BASTARDS.

20:18.785 --> 20:19.852
OKAY...

20:19.886 --> 20:23.089
WHAT ARE YOU
NOT TELLING ME?

20:24.724 --> 20:26.526
IT'S ME.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.928
I'M UP FOR A NEW JOB,
NEAL.

20:28.961 --> 20:32.799
RUNNING THE LONDON BRANCH
OF STERLING BOSCH.

20:34.901 --> 20:36.569
WOW. THAT'S...

20:36.603 --> 20:38.705
MY CHANCES
WERE EXCELLENT.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.707
BUT IF -- IF YOU LOSE
THE PERFUME BOTTLE...

20:40.740 --> 20:42.409
I LOSE ALL OF IT.

20:44.611 --> 20:46.245
I PROBABLY SHOULD HAVE
SAID SOMETHING SOONER.

20:46.279 --> 20:47.580
I --
NO, NO.

20:47.614 --> 20:48.948
I MEAN, WHY -- WHY WOULD YOU?
WE'RE JUST, YOU KNOW --

20:48.981 --> 20:50.550
AMIS-AMANTS.
RIGHT.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.084
WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M RUNNING AWAY

20:52.118 --> 20:53.920
TO AN ISLAND
OR SOMETHING.

20:53.953 --> 20:55.922
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
BRITAIN IS AN ISLAND.

20:55.955 --> 20:56.989
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:07.500 --> 21:08.568
[ SIGHS ]

21:08.601 --> 21:09.569
WOW.

21:09.602 --> 21:11.738
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:11.771 --> 21:14.641
YOU THINK OZ WILL LIKE IT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:14.674 --> 21:15.742
I DO.

21:15.775 --> 21:16.976
IT'S JUST, YOU KNOW,

21:17.009 --> 21:19.579
WITH EVERYTHING
THAT HE'S BEEN THROUGH,

21:19.612 --> 21:21.748
I-I JUST WANT
TO MAKE HIM HAPPY.

21:21.781 --> 21:23.750
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
THE SYSTEM FAILED HIM.

21:23.783 --> 21:25.818
I KNOW IT DID.

21:25.852 --> 21:28.588
AFTER OZ TOLD ME HIS STORY,
I LOOKED INTO IT.

21:28.621 --> 21:31.458
TURNS OUT IT'S NOT
THE FIRST TIME THIS COP LIED.

21:31.491 --> 21:34.661
HE HAS A HISTORY OF DISHING OUT
TRUMPED-UP CHARGES.

21:34.694 --> 21:36.329
DID YOU SHOW THIS
TO THE D.A.?

21:36.363 --> 21:38.164
YEAH, HIS PUBLIC DEFENDER
WOULDN'T LISTEN.

21:38.197 --> 21:39.932
I MEAN, HE SAID
WE DIDN'T STAND A CHANCE.

21:39.966 --> 21:42.268
REALLY?
THIS LOOKS DAMNING TO ME.

21:42.301 --> 21:43.503
I TOLD YOU.

21:43.536 --> 21:45.338
HE GOT A BUM RAP.

21:47.640 --> 21:50.443
Oz: SOUP'S ON, BABY!

21:50.477 --> 21:51.944
COMING!
HOPE YOU'RE HUNGRY.

21:51.978 --> 21:54.447
IF YOU DON'T EAT,
I'LL BE OFFENDED.

21:54.481 --> 21:55.848
SO, WHAT DO
YOU THINK?

21:55.882 --> 21:58.184
WHOA.

21:58.217 --> 21:59.318
[ LAUGHS ]
MM-MM-MM.

21:59.352 --> 22:00.653
WHAT?

22:00.687 --> 22:02.321
I WAS JUST WONDERING
HOW I GOT SO LUCKY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:05.992 --> 22:06.993
OH.

22:07.026 --> 22:09.161
WE SHOULD PROBABLY
UNTIE HIS HANDS.

22:09.195 --> 22:11.631
HANDS ONLY.
AND JUST FOR DINNER.

22:11.664 --> 22:12.732
ALL RIGHT?

22:16.235 --> 22:19.539
THANK YOU.

22:19.572 --> 22:22.709
IS THAT
A JAYER ECHEZEAUX?

22:22.742 --> 22:24.310
IS THAT
HOW YOU SAY IT?

22:24.343 --> 22:26.646
ALL I KNOW IS --
A CASE COSTS 12 GRAND.

22:26.679 --> 22:28.815
DON'T WORRY.
WE DIDN'T PAY FOR IT.

22:28.848 --> 22:30.182
[ LAUGHTER ]

22:30.216 --> 22:32.151
NOW, I'LL GO OUT ON A LIMB
AND SAY

22:32.184 --> 22:34.387
PENNY'S RING WASN'T
A HAND-ME-DOWN FROM GRANDMA?

22:34.421 --> 22:36.022
IT WAS MARILYN MONROE'S.

22:36.055 --> 22:37.557
[ SIGHS ]
I LOVE MARILYN.

22:37.590 --> 22:38.725
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY.

22:38.758 --> 22:40.393
I SPENT TWO YEARS
BEHIND BARS

22:40.427 --> 22:42.695
JUST PISSED OFF
THAT LIFE SCREWED ME OVER.

22:42.729 --> 22:44.330
AND THEN I MET PENNY,

22:44.363 --> 22:47.066
AND SHE MADE ME REALIZE
THAT YOU ONLY GET ONE LIFE.

22:47.099 --> 22:48.401
AND YOU BETTER LIVE IT.

22:50.937 --> 22:53.573
AND THIS CRIME SPREE
IS WHAT YOU CALL LIVING?

22:53.606 --> 22:56.743
THREE YEARS OF MY LIFE
HAS TO BE WORTH SOMETHING.

22:56.776 --> 22:58.344
THE WORLD OWES US THAT.

22:58.377 --> 22:59.679
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN
THE WORLD CATCHES UP TO YOU?

22:59.712 --> 23:01.080
WE WON'T LET IT.

23:01.113 --> 23:02.582
SO, PETER, UH,

23:02.615 --> 23:05.184
ELIZABETH TELLS ME THAT
YOU ARE A PROFESSOR AT COLUMBIA.

23:05.217 --> 23:06.252
MM-HMM.

23:06.285 --> 23:08.087
WHAT DO YOU TEACH?
JOURNALISM.

23:08.120 --> 23:09.922
NOW, I'M GUESSING,
BY THE AGE DIFFERENCE,

23:09.956 --> 23:11.691
THAT, UH,
LIZZY HERE WAS YOUR STUDENT.

23:11.724 --> 23:14.594
A LITTLE "HOT FOR TEACHER"
ACTION, HUH, LIZ?

23:14.627 --> 23:15.762
AM I RIGHT?

23:15.795 --> 23:17.096
GUILTY AS CHARGED.

23:17.129 --> 23:18.931
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

23:24.437 --> 23:27.273
Neal: STILL NOTHING
ON THE ELLEN FRONT?

23:27.306 --> 23:29.709
Mozzie:
WELL, APPARENTLY, THE IRS
CODES ITS FORMS DIFFERENTLY

23:29.742 --> 23:30.743
FOR PEOPLE IN WITSEC.

23:30.777 --> 23:32.579
THAT OR ELLEN
SPENT THREE YEARS

23:32.612 --> 23:34.581
AS A RIBBON DANCER
IN CIRCUS VARGAS.

23:34.614 --> 23:35.615
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:35.648 --> 23:37.283
I THINK I'D GO
WITH THE FIRST ONE.

23:37.316 --> 23:39.218
AVAILING YOURSELF
OF FEDERAL RESOURCES

23:39.251 --> 23:40.753
COULD SPEED ALONG
THE PROCESS.

23:40.787 --> 23:41.888
YEAH, I CAN'T.

23:41.921 --> 23:43.756
I PROMISED ELIZABETH
I WOULDN'T INVOLVE PETER.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.224
AND ONCE
YOU FIND THE BOX?

23:45.257 --> 23:47.760
I WANT MY FATHER TO COME BACK
AND LIVE A NORMAL LIFE.

23:47.794 --> 23:50.563
ELLEN'S EVIDENCE
CAN GIVE HIM THAT.

23:50.597 --> 23:53.432
AND WHILE WE'RE ON THE TOPIC
OF ITEMS JUST OUT OF REACH...

23:53.466 --> 23:54.601
AH,
THE PERFUME SEARCH.

23:54.634 --> 23:55.735
IF WE FIND IT,

23:55.768 --> 23:57.904
THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
SARA'S MOVING TO LONDON.

23:57.937 --> 24:00.072
AND YOU'RE AMBIVALENT
ABOUT WHAT THAT MEANS
TO THE TWO OF YOU.

24:00.106 --> 24:00.940
YEAH.

24:02.441 --> 24:03.943
DON'T GIVE ME
THAT LOOK.

24:03.976 --> 24:06.445
I KNOW I SAID WE WOULDN'T
GET SERIOUS AGAIN, BUT --

24:06.479 --> 24:08.447
LOOMING EXPIRATION DATE
IS FORCING YOU

24:08.481 --> 24:09.782
TO WONDER
IF YOU SHOULD.

24:09.816 --> 24:11.250
NEAL,
IT'S JUST A FANTASY.

24:11.283 --> 24:14.587
FOR GUYS LIKE US,
THE ONLY REGRET IS PERMANENCE.

24:14.621 --> 24:16.623
THAT'S JUST HOW IT IS.

24:16.656 --> 24:19.191
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

24:21.360 --> 24:22.762
DIANA, WHAT'S UP?

24:22.795 --> 24:24.163
YOU SAID PENNY CHASE WAS
WEARING HOOP EARRINGS, RIGHT?

24:24.196 --> 24:25.632
Yeah, why?

24:25.665 --> 24:28.434
E.R.T. FOUND AN EMERALD EARRING
UP THE STREET FROM THE BOUTIQUE,

24:28.467 --> 24:30.603
BUT WHAT'S STRANGE
IS THE BACKING WAS ATTACHED.

24:30.637 --> 24:32.805
ELIZABETH WAS WEARING
EMERALD EARRINGS WHEN THEY LEFT.

24:32.839 --> 24:34.106
SO SHE TOOK IT OFF
ON PURPOSE.

24:34.140 --> 24:36.275
IF SHE AND PETER WERE DELAYED
FOR A FEW MINUTES...

24:36.308 --> 24:37.443
YOU HEARD FROM HIM?

24:37.476 --> 24:39.311
I TRIED HIM AN HOUR AGO.
IT WENT TO HIS VOICEMAIL.

24:39.345 --> 24:40.613
I'M SURE THEY'RE FINE.

24:40.647 --> 24:41.981
YEAH.

24:44.884 --> 24:47.620
Oz: LOOK, ALL I'M SAYING IS
THAT COMPARED TO YOU,

24:47.654 --> 24:49.355
PETER HERE
SEEMS A LITTLE BORING.

24:49.388 --> 24:51.290
PLEASE.
I WISH HE WERE BORING.

24:51.323 --> 24:52.959
I HATE
THIS CONVERSATION.

24:52.992 --> 24:55.628
WAIT. SO, YOU'RE TELLING US
THAT HE'S NOT?

24:55.662 --> 24:57.296
YOU KNOW,
SOME OF THE STORIES HE'S COVERED

24:57.329 --> 24:58.531
HAVE BEEN
INCREDIBLY DANGEROUS.

24:58.565 --> 25:04.537
SOME NIGHTS, I LIE AWAKE
AND I CAN'T SLEEP, WORRYING.

25:04.571 --> 25:07.373
THE POINT IS --
I LIKE BORING,

25:07.406 --> 25:10.476
AND THERE'S NO ONE I'D RATHER
BE BORING WITH THAN THIS MAN.

25:10.509 --> 25:13.479
SO, TWO NIGHTS
IN AN OLD HOUSE IN VERMONT

25:13.512 --> 25:15.214
IS YOUR IDEA OF A PARTY?

25:15.247 --> 25:17.650
THE RUSTY EGRET.

25:17.684 --> 25:19.318
SURPRISE.

25:19.351 --> 25:21.487
I GUESS IT IS.
YOU'RE A WILD MAN, PETEY.

25:21.520 --> 25:22.521
[ LAUGHS ]

25:24.591 --> 25:26.358
Drop your dish.

25:26.392 --> 25:27.694
[ LAUGHS ]

25:29.395 --> 25:30.863
OH,
I'M GONNA CLEAN UP.

25:32.599 --> 25:34.166
OH!

25:34.200 --> 25:35.835
I'M SORRY.
NO, I'LL GET A BROOM.

25:35.868 --> 25:37.003
NO, NO, IT'S --
I'LL HELP.

25:37.036 --> 25:38.070
OH. I'LL GET IT,
I'LL GET IT.

25:38.104 --> 25:39.505
Penny:
DO WE HAVE A BAG?

25:39.538 --> 25:41.407
HEY, HONEY,
CAN YOU PLEASE GET ME A --

25:41.440 --> 25:43.375
WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

25:48.881 --> 25:51.517
SPECIAL AGENT
PETER BURKE?

25:59.425 --> 26:00.026
Diana:
EVERYONE LISTEN UP.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.262
OUR BOLO TURNED UP AGENT BURKE'S
CAR AT AN IMPOUND IN FLATBUSH.

26:03.295 --> 26:05.231
WE FOUND PETER AND ELIZABETH'S
CELLPHONES

26:05.264 --> 26:07.033
IN A DUMPSTER
TWO BLOCKS FROM THE BOUTIQUE.

26:07.066 --> 26:09.235
WE'RE ORDERING THE J.O.C.
STOOD UP UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE.

26:09.268 --> 26:10.870
WE HAVE TO ASSUME
THEY'VE BEEN TAKEN.

26:10.903 --> 26:12.872
SIMPSON, I WANT YOUR TEAM
TO STAY ON THE LETTERS.

26:12.905 --> 26:14.406
FOSTER,
PULL THE TRAFFIC-CAM FOOTAGE

26:14.440 --> 26:16.208
IN THE AREA
WHERE THE CAR WAS RECOVERED.

26:16.242 --> 26:17.777
AND FLAG
ANY MISSING-VEHICLE REPORTS.

26:17.810 --> 26:19.946
CHASE AND OSBOURNE ARE GONNA
NEED A NEW GETAWAY CAR.

26:19.979 --> 26:22.281
LET'S GO.
PETER'S COUNTING ON US.

26:24.450 --> 26:26.385
NEAL,
HOW COULD THIS HAPPEN?

26:26.418 --> 26:27.620
WRONG PLACE,
WRONG TIME.

26:27.654 --> 26:29.055
BUT THERE'S
A BRIGHT SIDE.

26:29.088 --> 26:30.923
A BRIGHT SIDE
TO KIDNAPPING?

26:30.957 --> 26:32.725
YEAH.
BALLISTICS CAME IN.

26:32.759 --> 26:35.895
OZ IS SHOOTING BLANKS.
WHY WOULD HE DO THAT?

26:35.928 --> 26:36.929
THEY DON'T WANT
TO HURT ANYONE.

26:36.963 --> 26:38.064
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
THEY WON'T.

26:38.097 --> 26:39.398
NO, IT DOESN'T.

26:39.431 --> 26:40.399
WHAT CAN I DO?

26:40.432 --> 26:41.768
HELP US
COMB THROUGH THESE LETTERS.

26:41.801 --> 26:43.569
IF WE BEAT THEM
TO THEIR NEXT TARGET,

26:43.602 --> 26:44.904
WE FIND
PETER AND ELIZABETH.

26:44.937 --> 26:48.240
BUT OZ BURIES HIS PROMISES
IN ROMANTIC SYMBOLISM,

26:48.274 --> 26:49.575
AND HE IS OPEN
TO INTERPRETATION.

26:49.608 --> 26:51.243
[ SIGHS ] THEN LET'S
GET TO INTERPRETING.

26:51.277 --> 26:52.411
WHERE DO YOU WANT
TO SET UP?

26:52.444 --> 26:53.612
MY PLACE HAS
A HUNGRY DOG

26:53.646 --> 26:55.081
AND A WINE-DRINKING
SPEED-READER.

26:55.114 --> 26:58.584
YOUR BRING THE PHOTO COPIES.
I'LL BRING THE COFFEE.

26:58.617 --> 27:00.419
Penny: OZ, THIS DOESN'T
HAVE TO CHANGE ANYTHING.

27:00.452 --> 27:01.587
WE JUST KIDNAPPED
AN FBI AGENT.

27:01.620 --> 27:02.755
YEAH,
BUT WE DIDN'T MEAN TO.

27:02.789 --> 27:04.423
YOU THINK
THEY CARE ABOUT THAT?

27:04.456 --> 27:06.092
PENNY'S RIGHT.
THIS IS A MISTAKE.

27:06.125 --> 27:07.927
OH, WE ARE THROUGH
TALKING TO YOU.

27:07.960 --> 27:09.328
OZ, LISTEN TO ME.

27:09.361 --> 27:11.263
THIS HAS GONE
FAR ENOUGH.

27:11.297 --> 27:13.933
YOUR BEST OPTION --
YOUR ONLY OPTION --

27:13.966 --> 27:16.502
IS TO LET US GO
AND TURN YOURSELVES IN.

27:16.535 --> 27:18.437
THAT'S YOUR ADVICE?
YES.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.673
I JUST GOT OUT,
AND YOU WANT ME TO WALK BACK IN?

27:25.644 --> 27:27.279
WE'RE NEVER
GONNA BE TOGETHER.

27:27.313 --> 27:28.314
NO. NO.

27:28.347 --> 27:30.449
WE'RE GONNA
WORK THIS OUT, OKAY?

27:30.482 --> 27:31.784
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

27:31.818 --> 27:35.955
DO YOU STILL WANT
TO GO FOR THE THIRD ACT?
YEAH.

27:35.988 --> 27:37.356
YEAH, WE GET IT.

27:37.389 --> 27:39.792
WE SKIP TOWN,
JUST LIKE WE PLANNED.

27:39.826 --> 27:42.795
[ CHUCKLES ]
OKAY,
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

27:42.829 --> 27:44.496
WE CAN'T
LET THEM GO NOW.

27:44.530 --> 27:46.999
MAYBE THEY COULD BE
OF SOME USE TO US.

27:48.667 --> 27:50.970
YEAH.

27:51.003 --> 27:53.973
Mozzie: I'VE BEEN THROUGH
THIS ENTIRE PILE TWICE NOW.

27:54.006 --> 27:56.342
IT STILL READS
LIKE A BAD ROMANCE NOVEL,

27:56.375 --> 27:57.977
WITH MORE MISSPELLINGS
AND REDACTIONS.

27:58.010 --> 27:59.979
THEY DON'T HAVE SPELL-CHECK
IN PRISON.

28:00.012 --> 28:03.149
WHAT THEY LACK IN TECHNIQUE
THEY MAKE UP FOR WITH HEART.

28:03.182 --> 28:05.151
DO THEY HAVE TO WRITE
EVERY DAY?

28:05.184 --> 28:08.554
"I LOVE YOU. I ADORE YOU.
I WORSHIP YOU."

28:08.587 --> 28:11.057
HOW MANY WAYS CAN THEY SAY
THE EXACT SAME THING?

28:11.090 --> 28:13.059
THIS MANY WAYS.

28:13.092 --> 28:14.560
[ SATCHMO WHINES ]

28:14.593 --> 28:16.729
MOZ, WILL YOU, UH --
YEAH, I'LL GET HIM.

28:16.763 --> 28:20.232
FRESH AIR -- THE ANTIDOTE
TO SENTIMENTAL DRIVEL.

28:20.266 --> 28:21.567
COME ON, SATCHMO.

28:21.600 --> 28:24.103
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

28:25.437 --> 28:26.906
[ SIGHS ]

28:26.939 --> 28:29.341
SO, LONDON.
HELL OF A CITY.

28:29.375 --> 28:30.509
IT IS.

28:30.542 --> 28:34.246
I SPENT THE SUMMER THERE
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER --

28:34.280 --> 28:35.714
WITH MY SISTER.

28:35.748 --> 28:38.550
MY PARENTS WARNED US
TO STAY AWAY FROM ISLINGTON,

28:38.584 --> 28:41.087
'CAUSE THAT'S WHERE
THE BAD KIDS HANG OUT.

28:41.120 --> 28:43.555
SO, OF COURSE,
WE WERE THERE EVERY NIGHT.

28:43.589 --> 28:44.723
OF COURSE.

28:44.757 --> 28:46.725
SMOKING CIGARETTES
WITH THE STREET ARTISTS

28:46.759 --> 28:48.260
AND FLIRTING
WITH THE BAD BOYS.

28:48.294 --> 28:49.261
MM-HMM.

28:49.295 --> 28:51.764
WELL, I DON'T SMOKE,
BUT I DO FLIRT.

28:51.798 --> 28:52.899
YEAH?
YEAH.

28:52.932 --> 28:55.067
YOU'RE ALSO
A VERY BAD BOY.

28:55.101 --> 28:56.602
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

28:56.635 --> 28:57.636
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

29:01.640 --> 29:03.709
I HOPE YOU GET THE JOB.

29:03.742 --> 29:06.245
NOT BECAUSE I WANT YOU
TO LEAVE --

29:06.278 --> 29:08.948
BECAUSE
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

29:11.283 --> 29:14.220
I HAVE TO ADMIT --
IT HAS BEEN A LOT OF FUN

29:14.253 --> 29:16.923
SPENDING TIME WITH YOU
UP IN THE CLOUDS.

29:16.956 --> 29:18.424
BUT THE GROUND BECKONS.

29:18.457 --> 29:19.625
WELL...

29:19.658 --> 29:23.896
"THERE IS NO SECURITY ON
THIS EARTH, ONLY OPPORTUNITY."

29:23.930 --> 29:26.432
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

29:26.465 --> 29:27.733
SEND ME A POSTCARD?

29:27.766 --> 29:31.270
YEAH. MORE THAN ONE.
LESS THAN 700.

29:31.303 --> 29:32.471
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

29:32.504 --> 29:33.906
DOES THAT MEAN
I GET A POEM?
MM-HMM.

29:33.940 --> 29:35.607
WILL YOU
USE SPELL-CHECK?
[ Chuckling ]
STOP IT.

29:38.444 --> 29:39.478
"IN THE CLOUDS."

29:39.511 --> 29:40.746
WHAT?

29:40.779 --> 29:42.581
NEAL,
OZ SAYS MULTIPLE TIMES

29:42.614 --> 29:44.750
THAT HIS
FAVORITE CHILDHOOD MEMORY

29:44.783 --> 29:47.987
IS WHEN HIS FATHER TOOK HIM
TO THE KENNEDY SPACE CENTER.

29:48.020 --> 29:49.421
YEAH, SOMETHING ABOUT WISHING
HE COULD FLY THROUGH THE CLOUDS

29:49.455 --> 29:50.589
AND OFF TO THE MOON.

29:50.622 --> 29:51.757
RIGHT.

29:51.790 --> 29:57.263
AND THEN TWO DAYS BEFORE
HE GETS OUT, HE WRITES THIS.

29:57.296 --> 29:59.966
"GIVE ME YOUR LOVE,
AND I'LL GIVE YOU THE MOON."

29:59.999 --> 30:01.667
SO WHAT IF HE'S GOING
TO GIVE HER THE MOON?

30:01.700 --> 30:03.135
I MEAN, NOT THE WHOLE THING,
BUT --

30:03.169 --> 30:04.470
MAYBE A PIECE OF IT.

30:09.808 --> 30:12.778
OKAY, NEAL, THERE'S ONLY
ONE MOON ROCK IN TOWN --

30:12.811 --> 30:13.779
FROM APOLLO 17.

30:13.812 --> 30:15.281
YEAH, WE SEE IT.

30:15.314 --> 30:17.316
IT'S ON DISPLAY AT THE NEW YORK
HALL OF SCIENCE IN QUEENS.

30:17.349 --> 30:19.318
YOU REALLY THINK
HE'S GONNA STEAL HER A ROCK?

30:19.351 --> 30:22.454
YEAH, OZ'S FINAL PROMISE TO
PENNY WAS TO GIVE HER THE MOON.

30:22.488 --> 30:24.123
WE GOT A HIT
ON PETER AND ELIZABETH.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.624
10 MINUTES AGO,
A STOLEN CAR

30:25.657 --> 30:27.459
USED ITS E-ZPass
AT THE MIDTOWN TUNNEL.

30:27.493 --> 30:29.361
WE GOT A SHOT OF IT
ON THE SECURITY CAMERA.

30:29.395 --> 30:30.462
IT'S THEM.
THEY'RE HITTING THE MUSEUM.

30:30.496 --> 30:32.631
I'LL MOBILIZE SWAT.
LET'S GO!

30:32.664 --> 30:33.799
ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

30:33.832 --> 30:35.634
GET MUSEUM SECURITY
ON THE PHONE.

30:35.667 --> 30:37.169
LET THEM KNOW WHAT'S COMING.

30:48.847 --> 30:51.683
Peter: FBI!
PLEASE OPEN THE DOOR.

30:53.752 --> 30:55.154
GOOD MORNING,
AGENT --

30:55.187 --> 30:56.655
Oz: DON'T MOVE.
I MEAN IT.

30:56.688 --> 30:58.190
SPECIAL AGENT
PETER BURKE.

30:58.224 --> 31:00.359
DO AS HE SAYS
AND YOU WON'T GET HURT.

31:00.392 --> 31:01.593
GET IN.

31:03.262 --> 31:06.532
HEY, BABY, WE'RE INSIDE.

31:09.401 --> 31:11.737
OPEN YOUR COAT.
COME ON.

31:11.770 --> 31:13.672
TAKE HIS GUN.
HMM?

31:13.705 --> 31:15.374
Yeah, get the gun.

31:17.209 --> 31:18.244
IN THE CHAIR.
COME ON.

31:20.947 --> 31:23.349
Oz: WHAT'S THE CODE
FOR INTERNAL SECURITY?

31:23.382 --> 31:24.383
Guard: 37294.

31:24.416 --> 31:26.185
I TOLD YOU --
YOU DON'T NEED ELIZABETH.

31:26.218 --> 31:28.754
KEEP ME AS YOUR HOSTAGE.
I WON'T CAUSE ANY TROUBLE.

31:28.787 --> 31:30.356
YEAH,
YOU WON'T CAUSE US ANY TROUBLE

31:30.389 --> 31:31.557
BECAUSE
WE GOT YOUR WIFE.

31:31.590 --> 31:33.025
HON, I'LL BE OKAY.

31:33.059 --> 31:34.426
YES, SHE WILL,

31:34.460 --> 31:37.363
AS LONG AS YOU DO
EXACTLY WHAT WE SAY.

31:51.577 --> 31:53.379
Sara:
THEY'RE ALREADY INSIDE.
Guard: WE'RE BEING ROBBED.

31:53.412 --> 31:55.547
CALL THE POLICE!
WE GOT TO FIND
ANOTHER WAY IN.

31:55.581 --> 31:56.882
NEAL, WE NEED TO WAIT
FOR THE FBI.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.050
LOOK,
IT'S PETER AND ELIZABETH.

31:58.084 --> 31:59.118
I'M NOT WAITING.
NEAL!

32:02.288 --> 32:03.922
Oz: HANDS.
[ PETER SIGHS ]

32:03.956 --> 32:07.726
YOU ARE ONLY MAKING THIS WORSE
FOR YOURSELF, OZ.

32:07.759 --> 32:08.727
QUIET.

32:08.760 --> 32:11.964
HAVE A SEAT,
BOTH OF YOU.

32:14.000 --> 32:16.302
THAT MOON ROCK'S THE MOST
VALUABLE THING IN THIS PLACE.

32:20.506 --> 32:22.074
Sara: NEAL, AT LEAST TELL ME
YOU HAVE A PLAN.

32:22.108 --> 32:24.076
LOOK, IF THEY'VE GOT
PETER AND ELIZABETH

32:24.110 --> 32:26.778
AND THE FBI SHOWS UP, THIS TURNS
INTO A HOSTAGE SITUATION,

32:26.812 --> 32:27.913
UNLESS...

32:27.946 --> 32:28.947
UNLESS WHAT?
YOU HAVE A BARGAINING CHIP?

32:28.981 --> 32:29.948
YEAH.

32:29.982 --> 32:32.418
I'M GONNA
STEAL THE MOON.

32:32.451 --> 32:34.420
NOT ALONE, YOU'RE NOT.

32:34.453 --> 32:37.089
IT'S PETER
AND ELIZABETH.

32:37.123 --> 32:38.657
ALL RIGHT.

32:43.829 --> 32:45.764
THAT'S IT?
THAT IS IT.

32:45.797 --> 32:48.667
WELL, AS FAR AS PRICELESS
OBJECTS GO, I'M NOT IMPRESSED.

32:48.700 --> 32:51.970
IT'S 4 1/2 BILLION YEARS OLD,
200,000 MILES FROM HOME,

32:52.004 --> 32:54.506
AND WORTH 100 TIMES
ITS WEIGHT IN GOLD.

32:54.540 --> 32:57.343
Penny: 37294.
THAT DID IT!

32:57.376 --> 32:58.677
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

32:58.710 --> 33:00.112
GOOD JOB, PEN.

33:00.146 --> 33:01.113
HEY, OZ, ISN'T THAT --

33:01.147 --> 33:02.481
YEAH,
FROM THE PERFUME SHOP.

33:02.514 --> 33:03.682
THEY'RE STEALING
THE MOON ROCK.

33:03.715 --> 33:04.783
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON?

33:04.816 --> 33:07.119
HEY, YOU --
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME.

33:07.153 --> 33:08.654
I'M NOT
LEAVING MY WIFE.

33:08.687 --> 33:09.721
I BEG TO DIFFER.

33:10.856 --> 33:12.824
ALL RIGHT,
IF ANYTHING GOES WRONG,

33:12.858 --> 33:14.460
JUST MEET ME
IN THE LOBBY.

33:14.493 --> 33:15.461
PEN, LOOK AT ME.

33:15.494 --> 33:17.963
THIS IS WHAT WE WANTED,
REMEMBER?

33:17.996 --> 33:19.631
ALL RIGHT.

33:19.665 --> 33:21.467
NOW, BURKE.

33:21.500 --> 33:23.869
COME ON.

33:27.373 --> 33:28.707
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
GO THROUGH WITH THIS.

33:28.740 --> 33:29.708
YOU KNOW THAT.

33:29.741 --> 33:30.876
I KINDA DO.

33:35.181 --> 33:38.150
I'VE NEVER ACTUALLY SEEN
YOU STEAL ANYTHING BEFORE.

33:38.184 --> 33:41.187
WELL, THAT IS ONE OF THE PERKS
OF BEING MY PLUS-ONE.

33:43.422 --> 33:45.057
LET'S GO.

33:45.091 --> 33:47.393
HEY, SINATRA,
YOU WANT TO TELL ME WHY

33:47.426 --> 33:49.828
YOU AND BATON GIRL
ARE STEALING MY ROCK?

33:49.861 --> 33:50.829
OH, YOUR ROCK?

33:50.862 --> 33:52.664
THAT'S FUNNY,
BECAUSE ACCORDING TO

33:52.698 --> 33:54.833
ARTICLE VI OF THE 1967
U.N. OUTER SPACE TREATY,

33:54.866 --> 33:55.834
IT'S NOT YOURS.

33:55.867 --> 33:57.736
NEAL.
I GOT THIS, PETER.

33:57.769 --> 34:00.906
OH, YOU TWO KNOW EACH OTHER.
THAT'S CUTE.

34:00.939 --> 34:03.175
NOW GIVE ME
THE DAMN ROCK.

34:03.209 --> 34:04.376
I DON'T THINK SO.

34:04.410 --> 34:05.844
BALLISTICS CONFIRMED
YOU'RE SHOOTING BLANKS.

34:05.877 --> 34:06.945
NEAL.
WHAT?

34:09.948 --> 34:11.683
HE HAS MY GUN.

34:11.717 --> 34:13.018
OKAY.

34:13.051 --> 34:15.954
SO,
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

34:19.125 --> 34:21.727
SARA, YOUR BATON.

34:22.461 --> 34:23.729
I'M WARNING YOU.

34:23.762 --> 34:25.030
AND I'M EDUCATING YOU.

34:25.063 --> 34:26.732
THE MOON
HAS NO ATMOSPHERE,

34:26.765 --> 34:29.067
NO FREE OXYGEN,
AND NO SURFACE MOISTURE.

34:29.101 --> 34:31.370
THAT'S WHY THIS ROCK
IS VACUUM-SEALED IN NITROGEN.

34:31.403 --> 34:33.105
ONCE IT'S EXPOSED
TO OUR ATMOSPHERE,

34:33.139 --> 34:35.107
IT CRUMBLES TO DUST
IN A MATTER OF SECONDS.

34:35.141 --> 34:37.709
SARA.
I DO LIKE
TO SMASH THINGS.

34:37.743 --> 34:39.278
YEAH, AND I'LL SHOOT
BOTH OF YOU.

34:39.311 --> 34:41.280
NOT BEFORE ONE OF US
SMASHES YOUR ROCK.

34:41.313 --> 34:42.781
LET PETER GO
AND IT'S YOURS.

34:42.814 --> 34:44.216
EVERYBODY WINS.

34:44.250 --> 34:45.384
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:45.417 --> 34:46.585
HAVE IT YOUR WAY.
SARA.

34:46.618 --> 34:47.753
WAIT!

34:54.493 --> 34:56.395
ENJOY.

34:56.428 --> 34:58.063
[ SIGHS ]
MATTER OF SECONDS, HUH?

34:58.096 --> 34:59.798
I MAY HAVE EXAGGERATED
A LITTLE BIT.

34:59.831 --> 35:02.268
IT WOULD HAVE TURNED TO DUST
IN ANOTHER BILLION YEARS.

35:02.301 --> 35:04.403
HE'S NOT MAKING IT
OUT OF HERE.

35:04.436 --> 35:07.072
YOU AND SARA
EXIT THE SAME WAY YOU CAME IN.

35:07.105 --> 35:10.108
LET THE FBI KNOW THAT PENNY
AND OZ ARE BOTH ARMED.

35:10.142 --> 35:11.310
PETER,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

35:11.343 --> 35:12.778
TO GET MY WIFE BACK.

35:14.980 --> 35:17.082
[ SIGHS ]

35:17.115 --> 35:19.751
YOU'VE BEEN A CRIMINAL
LESS THAN A WEEK, PENNY.

35:19.785 --> 35:21.953
I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE CUT OUT FOR THIS.

35:21.987 --> 35:24.956
IT'S BETTER TO BURN BRIGHT THAN
SLOWLY FADE AWAY, LIKE YOU --

35:24.990 --> 35:26.925
LIKE WHAT?
PETER AND ME?

35:26.958 --> 35:27.926
WE ARE NOT BORING.

35:27.959 --> 35:29.094
[ LAUGHS ]

35:29.127 --> 35:31.763
HELL, THIS IS NOT EVEN
MY FIRST KIDNAPPING.

35:31.797 --> 35:33.265
SERIOUSLY?

35:33.299 --> 35:34.433
YEAH.

35:34.466 --> 35:36.768
EVERY MORNING
MY HUSBAND WALKS OUT THE DOOR,

35:36.802 --> 35:39.271
A PART OF ME WORRIES
IF HE EVER WALKS BACK IN.

35:39.305 --> 35:41.139
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THAT FEELS LIKE?

35:41.173 --> 35:42.274
YEAH. I DO.

35:42.308 --> 35:43.775
THEN STOP HIM
BEFORE HE GETS HURT.

35:43.809 --> 35:45.344
YOU DIDN'T STOP PETER.

35:45.377 --> 35:46.445
I TRIED.

35:46.478 --> 35:48.280
BUT WHETHER
I LIKE IT OR NOT,

35:48.314 --> 35:50.849
PEOPLE LIKE YOU
HAPPEN TO PEOPLE LIKE US.

35:50.882 --> 35:51.950
THAT'S LIFE.

35:51.983 --> 35:53.185
ELIZABETH --

35:53.219 --> 35:55.187
YOU KNOW, I'M SUPPOSED TO BE
ON A ROMANTIC WEEKEND

35:55.221 --> 35:57.289
WITH MY HUSBAND RIGHT NOW,
AND INSTEAD,

35:57.323 --> 36:01.126
I'M STUCK HERE WITH YOU,
LIVING YOUR MOMENT.

36:01.159 --> 36:04.496
WHICH, BY THE WAY,
JUST CAUGHT UP WITH YOU.

36:05.897 --> 36:07.132
WHAT?

36:07.165 --> 36:08.133
NO!

36:08.166 --> 36:09.468
PENNY, IT'S OVER.

36:09.501 --> 36:10.869
OZ IS GOING
BACK TO PRISON.

36:10.902 --> 36:12.471
NO, HE IS NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.973
WE PROMISED EACH OTHER
THAT WE WOULD NOT GET CAUGHT.

36:15.006 --> 36:18.009
IF IT IS OVER FOR HIM,
THEN IT IS OVER FOR ME, TOO.

36:19.378 --> 36:21.513
I WAS NEVER
GONNA SHOOT YOU,

36:21.547 --> 36:24.216
JUST LIKE
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA SHOOT ME.

36:24.250 --> 36:25.717
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:25.751 --> 36:28.019
I GUESS NEITHER OF US
ARE CUT OUT FOR THIS, HUH?

36:28.053 --> 36:30.522
I NEVER WANTED
TO BE GOOD AT THIS.

36:32.424 --> 36:34.393
PENNY.

36:35.594 --> 36:36.728
Neal: HEY.

36:36.762 --> 36:38.063
CAFFREY! WHERE THE HELL
DID YOU COME FROM?

36:38.096 --> 36:39.231
INSIDE.
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

36:39.265 --> 36:40.566
PETER AND ELIZABETH
ARE IN THERE.

36:40.599 --> 36:41.900
SO ARE PENNY AND OZ,
AND THEY'RE ARMED.

36:41.933 --> 36:43.034
WITH
PETER'S GUN.

36:43.068 --> 36:44.069
Jones: OKAY,
YOU GUYS HANG BACK.

36:44.102 --> 36:45.170
Diana: LET'S MOVE IN!

36:45.203 --> 36:46.538
LET'S GO!

36:50.542 --> 36:52.511
EL.
PENNY AND OZ
JUST WENT OUT FRONT.

36:52.544 --> 36:54.045
IT'S OKAY.
BUILDING'S SURROUNDED.

36:54.079 --> 36:55.247
THAT'S JUST IT --
I THINK THEY'RE PLANNING

36:55.281 --> 36:56.515
ON GOING OUT THERE
LIKE BONNIE AND CLYDE.

36:56.548 --> 36:57.549
HONEY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:57.583 --> 36:59.518
WHAT? THEY NEED OUR HELP.
COME ON.

36:59.551 --> 37:01.353
NO, THEY'RE NOT --
DAMN IT.

37:09.795 --> 37:10.929
Penny: HEY.

37:13.732 --> 37:18.236
COME OUT PEACEFULLY
WITH YOUR HANDS IN THE AIR.

37:23.409 --> 37:25.577
OH, MY GOD.

37:25.611 --> 37:28.614
IT'S THE MOST BEAUTIFUL THING
I'VE EVER SEEN.

37:30.582 --> 37:31.917
I GOT YOU THE MOON.

37:35.253 --> 37:39.057
COME OUT QUIETLY.
RAISE YOUR HANDS.

37:39.090 --> 37:40.592
YOU READY?

37:42.428 --> 37:45.897
WE DON'T WANT TO HURT YOU.

37:45.931 --> 37:47.733
JUST STAY CLOSE,
ALL RIGHT?

37:47.766 --> 37:48.767
MAYBE WE CAN --

37:48.800 --> 37:50.802
PENNY, OZ, COME ON.

37:50.836 --> 37:52.738
STAY BACK, LIZ.
YOU CAN'T GO OUT THERE.

37:52.771 --> 37:54.906
YOU KNOW WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.
JUST TELL HIM.

37:54.940 --> 37:56.808
PENNY, DON'T LISTEN
TO HER, OKAY?

37:56.842 --> 37:58.644
WE HAVE
A LOVE FOR THE AGES.

37:58.677 --> 38:00.412
Peter:
OZ, LISTEN TO ME.

38:00.446 --> 38:02.080
THERE'S
A SWAT TEAM OUT THERE

38:02.113 --> 38:04.249
WITH AUTOMATIC WEAPONS
AND BODY ARMOR.

38:04.282 --> 38:06.485
YOU TRY TO SHOOT YOUR WAY
OUT OF THERE,

38:06.518 --> 38:08.320
AND THEY WILL KILL
BOTH OF YOU.

38:08.354 --> 38:10.155
YEAH,
NOT IF I KILL THEM FIRST.

38:10.188 --> 38:12.458
DON'T BE A FOOL,
OZ.

38:12.491 --> 38:14.092
THIS ISN'T YOU.

38:14.125 --> 38:15.761
I KNOW
YOU SERVED THREE YEARS

38:15.794 --> 38:18.430
FOR SOMETHING THAT
SHOULD HAVE BEEN A MISDEMEANOR.

38:18.464 --> 38:20.298
YOU GOT A BUM RAP,
AND I'M SORRY.

38:20.332 --> 38:22.768
YOU WERE USING BLANKS
SO NO ONE GOT HURT,

38:22.801 --> 38:25.771
BUT THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT'S
ABOUT TO HAPPEN OUT THERE

38:25.804 --> 38:27.639
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

38:27.673 --> 38:29.274
YOU LOVE HER?

38:29.307 --> 38:30.442
YEAH.

38:30.476 --> 38:33.979
DO YOU REALLY
LOVE HER, OZ?
YES!

38:34.012 --> 38:38.149
REAL LOVE...
IS FIGHTING LIKE HELL

38:38.183 --> 38:41.119
TO HOLD ON TO EVERY MOMENT
YOU HAVE WITH HER.

38:41.152 --> 38:43.989
IT'S MAKING
A LIFE TOGETHER

38:44.022 --> 38:48.126
AND MAKING IT WORK
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS.

38:48.159 --> 38:50.629
YOU WANT A LOVE
FOR THE AGES?

38:50.662 --> 38:52.364
I THINK THAT'S GREAT.

38:52.398 --> 38:54.132
PROVE IT.

38:54.165 --> 38:57.803
MAKE IT LAST.

38:57.836 --> 39:02.207
[ Voice breaking ]
LISTEN, THEY'RE JUST GONNA
TAKE ME AWAY FROM HER.

39:02.240 --> 39:03.208
NO.

39:03.241 --> 39:06.044
THEY CAN TAKE AWAY
A LOT OF THINGS,

39:06.077 --> 39:10.148
BUT THEY'LL NEVER TAKE AWAY
WHAT YOU TWO HAVE TOGETHER.

39:10.181 --> 39:13.218
YOU GO OUT THERE,
AND IT ENDS.

39:17.523 --> 39:18.924
GIVE ME THE GUN,
OZ.

39:30.368 --> 39:32.904
Peter: IT COULD HAVE
GOTTEN PRETTY UGLY BACK THERE.

39:32.938 --> 39:34.506
YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I --

39:34.540 --> 39:35.907
I DO.

39:35.941 --> 39:38.844
I'M JUST GLAD
YOU'RE OKAY.

39:38.877 --> 39:41.212
Diana: TAKE HIM AWAY.

39:41.246 --> 39:42.548
SO, WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN?

39:42.581 --> 39:43.882
SHE'LL GET PROBATION,

39:43.915 --> 39:46.017
AND THIS TIME,
HE'LL GET A FAIR TRIAL.

39:46.051 --> 39:47.052
WRITE ME?

39:47.085 --> 39:49.555
EVERY DAY.

39:52.090 --> 39:54.092
Man: COME ON, SIR.

39:55.594 --> 39:57.228
WE STILL HAVE TO
GIVE OUR STATEMENTS,

39:57.262 --> 39:59.698
BUT IT'S NOT TOO LATE
TO TRY AND GET AWAY.

39:59.731 --> 40:01.533
MAYBE NOT THE RUSTY EGRET,
BUT --

40:01.567 --> 40:03.935
I JUST WANT
TO GO HOME.

40:03.969 --> 40:04.936
YEAH.

40:04.970 --> 40:06.772
FIRST...

40:08.106 --> 40:09.407
THEY FOUND IT.
MM-HMM.

40:09.441 --> 40:10.442
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:11.910 --> 40:13.078
THANKS, HON.

40:18.784 --> 40:20.118
NICE.

40:20.151 --> 40:21.587
GREAT.

40:21.620 --> 40:23.889
OKAY.

40:23.922 --> 40:25.056
HEY.
HI.

40:25.090 --> 40:28.560
I JUST GAVE STERLING BOSCH
THE GOOD NEWS.

40:28.594 --> 40:30.061
WELL,
HERE'S SOME MORE.

40:30.095 --> 40:31.262
ISN'T THIS EVIDENCE?

40:31.296 --> 40:32.898
NOBODY'S
GONNA MISS IT,

40:32.931 --> 40:36.768
AS LONG AS IT'S BACK
TOMORROW MORNING.

40:36.802 --> 40:39.070
HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
ABOUT BEING MY PLUS-ONE TONIGHT,

40:39.104 --> 40:40.405
NO STRINGS ATTACHED?

40:40.438 --> 40:42.440
YOU KNOW
I LIKE A GOOD PARTY.

40:43.441 --> 40:44.810
THANK YOU.

40:44.843 --> 40:45.811
YEAH.

40:45.844 --> 40:47.278
[ LAUGHS ]

40:56.955 --> 40:58.624
Peter: YOU ASKED NEAL
TO LIE TO ME.

40:58.657 --> 41:00.659
YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT
TO BE UPSET,

41:00.692 --> 41:02.628
BUT YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I DID IT.

41:02.661 --> 41:04.329
TO PROTECT ME.
I GET THAT.

41:04.362 --> 41:07.666
I KNEW YOU WOULDN'T LET IT GO,
EVEN AFTER THE CAR ACCIDENT.

41:07.699 --> 41:11.102
BUT, HON, THE ONE THING THAT
TRULY SCARES ME IS LOSING YOU.

41:11.136 --> 41:12.638
I HAD TO DO SOMETHING.

41:12.671 --> 41:15.306
NEAL AND I
WILL ALWAYS HAVE SECRETS,

41:15.340 --> 41:17.475
BUT YOU AND I --
WE DON'T.

41:19.477 --> 41:21.179
NO MORE SECRETS.

41:21.212 --> 41:22.681
STARTING NOW.

41:22.714 --> 41:24.850
THERE WAS A FILE
THAT INDICATED

41:24.883 --> 41:27.953
WHERE ELLEN MIGHT HAVE
HIDDEN THE EVIDENCE BOX.

41:27.986 --> 41:29.788
I CHECKED IT
FOR PRINTS.

41:29.821 --> 41:31.456
IT WAS HERE
IN THE HOUSE.

41:31.489 --> 41:33.959
NEAL FOUND IT,
LIKE I HOPED HE WOULD.

41:33.992 --> 41:36.294
YOU WANT HIM
TO DOG-SIT SATCHMO.

41:36.327 --> 41:37.696
I'M HELPING HIS SEARCH

41:37.729 --> 41:39.464
WITHOUT PUTTING MYSELF
IN HARM'S WAY.

41:39.497 --> 41:40.799
AND YOU DIDN'T
WANT ME TO KNOW --

41:40.832 --> 41:42.467
BECAUSE I DIDN'T
WANT YOU TO WORRY.

41:42.500 --> 41:45.036
NO MORE SECRETS.

41:45.070 --> 41:47.305
SO NOW THAT
WE'RE ON THE SAME PAGE,

41:47.338 --> 41:49.307
WHAT ABOUT
YOU AND NEAL?

41:49.340 --> 41:51.009
HE TOOK THE BAIT.
NOW WHAT?

41:51.042 --> 41:52.544
HMM.

41:52.578 --> 41:54.045
Neal: YOU CRACKED IT?

41:54.079 --> 41:55.981
IT'S A GOVERNMENT CODE.
OF COURSE I DID.

41:56.014 --> 41:59.551
IT TURNS OUT
THAT EMPLOYER I.D. NUMBER

41:59.585 --> 42:02.721
IS FOR A SECURITY COMPANY
NAMED GRIFFIN-MOORE,

42:02.754 --> 42:06.558
WHICH IS LINKED
TO THE 50th FLOOR

42:06.592 --> 42:08.026
OF THE EMPIRE STATE
BUILDING.

42:10.395 --> 42:14.232
LET'S GET THAT BOX
AND BRING MY FATHER HOME.
